      "span_text": "In the 1970s there were reports of large joint effusions and widespread tissue destruction following total hip replacement (THR) with McKee-Farrar devices.  In 2005 Willert et al  described the histological appearance of periprosthetic tissues surrounding failed metal-on-metal joint replacements and suggested a lymphocytedominant delayed-type hypersensitivity reaction, aseptic lymphocyte-dominated vasculitis-associated lesion (ALVAL), as a potential explanation."
